BioMixer is a Web-based environment for visualizing and exploring biomedical ontologies. It is the underlying technology for the visualization components found in BioPortal(http://bioportal.bioontology.org/), the worldâ€™s most comprehensive repository of biomedical ontologies.

BioMixer's development is supported by the National Center for Biomedical Ontology (NCBO), the NHGRI, the NHLBI, the NIH Common Fund under Grant #U54-HG004028, and an IBM CAS PhD Fellowship.